article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- — Abe Johnson had 16 points in Army's 65-50 win over Boston University on Wednesday night. Johnson also added six rebounds for the Black Knights (9-17, 5-8 Patriot League). Josh Scovens added 15 points while shooting 6 of 10 from the field and 2 for 5 from the line, and he also had three blocks. Ryan Curry shot 5 for 10, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc to finish with 14 points. The Terriers (10-16, 5-8) were led by Matai Baptiste, who posted nine points, two steals and two blocks. Ben Palacios added nine points for Boston University. In addition, Nic Nobili had eight points and eight rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
